{
    "name": "Bernstein-Vazirani",
    "description": "\nThe Bernstein-Vazirani algorithm is a quantum algorithm proposed in [[1997, Bernstein and Vazirani]](https://epubs.siam.org/doi/10.1137/S0097539796300921) to solve the following problem.\n\n**Problem**. Given $x \\in \\\\{ 0, 1 \\\\}^N$ for some $N = 2^n$, such that $x_i = (i \\cdot s) \\mod 2$ for some unknown $s \\in \\\\{ 0, 1 \\\\}^n$. Determine $s$.\n\n<details>\n<summary>Bernstein-Vazirani algorithm</summary>\n\nDenote by $\\mathcal{O}$ the oracle which acts as $\\mathcal{O} \\ket{i} = (-1)^{x_i} \\ket{i}$ for all $i \\in \\\\{ 0, 1 \\\\}^n$.\n\n1. Start with the $n$-qubit state $\\ket{0^n}$.\n2. Apply a Hadamard gate to each qubit to obtain the state\n\\\\[ \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2^n}} \\sum_{i \\in \\\\{ 0, 1 \\\\}^n } \\ket{i} . \\\\]\n3. Apply the oracle $\\mathcal{O}$ to obtain the state\n\\\\[ \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2^n}} \\sum_{i \\in \\\\{ 0, 1 \\\\}^n} (-1)^{x_i} \\ket{i} = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2^n}} \\sum_{i \\in \\\\{ 0, 1 \\\\}^n} (-1)^{i \\cdot s} \\ket{i} . \\\\]\n4. Apply a Hadamard gate to each qubit to obtain the state $\\ket{s}$.\n5. Measure the qubits to find $s$.\n\n</details>\n\n**Experiment**. Given a number $n$, a secret $s \\in \\\\{0, 1\\\\}^n$ is constructed deterministically. The task is to determine $s$ using the Bernstein-Vazirani algorithm. The oracle $\\mathcal{O}$ is implemented as a sequence of CNOT gates, one for each control qubit $i = 1, \\ldots, n$ with $s_i = 1$, where the target is an auxillary qubit in the state $\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} (\\ket{0} - \\ket{1})$. The circuit is run for $1,000$ shots.\n\n**Metrics**. The _fidelity_ is defined as the fraction of shots resulting in the secret $s$.\n",
    "params": {
        "n": "int"
    },
    "metrics": [
        "fidelity",
        "entropy"
    ],
